704302f-a.title: Brooklyn: Flatbush Avenue - Avenue J
704302f-a.text:
(1)
1754 Flatbush Ave., west side, at the intersection of Ave. J. and
Tast 35th Street. This house was on the Stoothoff Farm, built by that
family. It was occupied by Richard Coe in 1860, by V. K. Stephenson in
1873 and by the Amersfort Nursery in 1922, when it was owned by John B. Lott.
Since 1922, this house has been moved, though its present location is un-
known.
1922.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, another view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
